#: source/work/doc.php:11
msgid "Security Header Generator Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:12
msgid "This plugin generates the proper security HTTP response headers and generates a Content Security Policy if configured to do so"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:13
msgid "Install"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:15
msgid "Download the plugin, unzip it, and upload to your sites"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:15
msgid "directory"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:17
msgid "You can also upload it directly to your Plugins admin"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:20
msgid "Activate the plugin through the \"Plugins\" menu in WordPress"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:23
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:24
msgid "Head over to the admin section of your site and click \"Security Headers\", configure how you need it to be configured. The configured headers will automatically be implemented."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:26
msgid "IMPORTANT: Hosting Environment Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:27
msgid "If your hosting environment is already setting these headers, most likely your settings in this plugin will <strong>NOT</strong> override the values you specify"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:28
msgid "If this is the case, please check with your hosting company or review your server configuration for headers being set. The plugin will do its best to override them, but in some environments this is just not possible"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:30
msgid "Settings Overview"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:34
msgid "Standard Security Headers Tab"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:35
msgid "This tab controls the basic security headers that protect your website from common attacks and vulnerabilities."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:38, source/work/doc.php:308, source/work/doc.php:440
msgid "Apply to Admin"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:40
msgid "Choose whether to apply these security headers to the WordPress admin area in addition to your public-facing website. Enabling this provides protection for your admin panel as well."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:44
msgid "Apply to the REST API"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:46
msgid "Choose whether to apply these headers to your WordPress REST API. <strong>NOTE:</strong> Because of how WordPress works, enabling this will also apply headers to the admin areas. Test thoroughly after enabling to ensure nothing breaks."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:50
msgid "Strict Transport Security"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:53
msgid "This forces browsers to only access your site over HTTPS (secure connections), preventing downgrade attacks where someone might try to force an insecure HTTP connection."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:56, source/work/doc.php:78, source/work/doc.php:99, source/work/doc.php:116, source/work/doc.php:133, source/work/doc.php:150, source/work/doc.php:164, source/work/doc.php:190, source/work/doc.php:202, source/work/doc.php:216, source/work/doc.php:230, source/work/doc.php:251, source/work/doc.php:273, source/work/doc.php:302, source/work/doc.php:436
msgid "Learn more:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:62
msgid "Configuration options:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:64
msgid "Cache Age:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:64
msgid "How long (in seconds) browsers should remember to only use HTTPS. Default is 31536000 (1 year)."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:65
msgid "Include Subdomains:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:65
msgid "Apply this rule to all subdomains (like blog.yoursite.com, shop.yoursite.com). Only enable if ALL your subdomains use HTTPS."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:66
msgid "Preload:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:66
msgid "Submit your site to browsers' preload lists for maximum security. If enabled, change Cache Age to 63072000 (2 years). Learn more:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:72
msgid "Frame Sources"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:75
msgid "Controls whether other websites can display your site in an iframe or frame. This prevents \"clickjacking\" attacks where attackers trick users by embedding your site invisibly."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:84, source/work/doc.php:236, source/work/doc.php:257, source/work/doc.php:279
msgid "Options:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:86
msgid "Block all websites from framing your site (most secure)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:87
msgid "Only allow your own domain to frame your site (useful if you need iframes on your own site)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:93
msgid "Access Control Methods"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:96
msgid "Controls which HTTP request methods (like GET, POST, etc.) external websites can use when accessing your site. This is useful for API security."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:105
msgid "Select which methods to allow. Most public websites need at least GET (for viewing pages). Clicking \"Allow All\" will check or uncheck all options. <strong>Note:</strong> Unselected methods will be blocked."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:110
msgid "Access Control Credentials"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:113
msgid "Allows browsers to send cookies and authentication information when JavaScript makes requests to your site. Useful for AJAX-based features and API calls that require user authentication."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:122
msgid "Default is Yes. Most modern websites need this enabled for JavaScript-driven features to work properly."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:127
msgid "Access Control Origin"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:130
msgid "Specifies which external websites can access your site's resources. This helps prevent unauthorized cross-site requests."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:139
msgid "Enter a specific domain (like <code>https://example.com</code>) or use <code>*</code> to allow all domains. If left empty, defaults to <code>*</code>."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:144
msgid "Prevent MimeType Sniffing"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:147
msgid "Stops browsers from trying to \"guess\" the type of files you serve. This prevents attackers from disguising malicious files as safe ones."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:158
msgid "Origin Referrers"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:161
msgid "Controls how much information about your site is shared when users click links to external websites. This protects user privacy."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:170
msgid "Policy options (from most private to least private):"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:172
msgid "Share no information at all"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:173
msgid "Only share your domain name, only on secure (HTTPS) connections (recommended)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:174
msgid "Only share your domain name"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:175
msgid "Share full URL within your own site, but only domain for external sites"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:176
msgid "Share full URL on your site, domain only for external sites (on secure connections)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:177
msgid "Share full URL on your site, domain only for external sites"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:178
msgid "Share full URL except when moving from HTTPS to HTTP"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:179
msgid "Always share full URL (least private)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:185
msgid "Force Downloads"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:188
msgid "Forces certain files to be downloaded rather than opened directly in the browser. This adds an extra layer of security for file handling."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:196
msgid "Cross Domain Origins"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:199
msgid "Blocks cross-domain access for PDFs and Flash content embedded on your site. This prevents certain types of attacks using these file types."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:210
msgid "Upgrade Insecure Requests"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:213
msgid "Automatically upgrades all insecure (HTTP) requests to secure (HTTPS) requests. This ensures all resources load securely even if old links reference HTTP."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:224
msgid "Cross Origin Embedder Policy"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:227
msgid "Controls how your site can embed resources from other domains. This prevents certain types of attacks involving embedded content."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:238
msgid "Allow embedding external resources without explicit permission (default, less secure)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:239
msgid "Only allow resources explicitly marked as embeddable (more secure, may require configuration)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:245
msgid "Cross Origin Resource Policy"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:248
msgid "Controls which websites can load resources (images, scripts, etc.) from your site. This prevents unauthorized use of your content."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:259
msgid "Only your exact domain can use your resources (most secure)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:260
msgid "Your domain and subdomains can use your resources"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:261
msgid "Any website can use your resources (least secure)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:267
msgid "Cross Origin Opener Policy"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:270
msgid "Controls whether other websites can access your site when opened in popups or new tabs. This prevents certain cross-site attacks."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:281
msgid "Allow normal popup/tab behavior (default)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:282
msgid "Allow popups but isolate from other origins"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:283
msgid "Complete isolation from other origins (most secure)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:292
msgid "Content Security Policy Tab"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:293
msgid "Content Security Policy (CSP) is an advanced security feature that controls which external resources your website can load. This prevents many types of attacks including Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:296
msgid "Generate CSP"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:299
msgid "Enable this to create a Content Security Policy for your site. This will show many additional fields where you can specify which external resources (scripts, styles, images, etc.) are allowed to load."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:301
msgid "Enter external domains in the Source fields using a space-separated list (example: <code>cdn.example.com fonts.google.com</code>)"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:310
msgid "Choose whether to apply the Content Security Policy to your WordPress admin area as well as the public site. <strong>Warning:</strong> This may break admin features if not configured correctly. Test thoroughly."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:314
msgid "CSP Presets"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:316
msgid "Quick start templates are available to help you configure CSP for common scenarios:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:318
msgid "WordPress Core Only (Strict):"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:319, source/work/inc/kcp-cspgen-presets.php:41
msgid "Minimal external sources - only WordPress.org, Gravatar, and Google Fonts. Good starting point for basic sites."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:322
msgid "WooCommerce Compatible:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:323, source/work/inc/kcp-cspgen-presets.php:46
msgid "WordPress Core plus payment gateways (PayPal, Stripe), common WooCommerce extensions, and analytics."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:326
msgid "Page Builder Friendly:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:327, source/work/inc/kcp-cspgen-presets.php:51
msgid "WordPress Core plus Google Fonts, video embeds, CDN sources. Allows inline styles/scripts required for Elementor/Divi."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:330
msgid "Locked Down (Maximum Security):"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:331, source/work/inc/kcp-cspgen-presets.php:56
msgid "Self only for most directives. No inline/eval. Minimal external sources. Best for static/admin-only sites."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:334
msgid "Development/Testing:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:335, source/work/inc/kcp-cspgen-presets.php:61
msgid "Permissive settings. Allows localhost and common development tools. Good for staging environments."
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:338, source/work/doc.php:410
msgid "Important:"
msgstr ""

#: source/work/doc.php:339
msgid "Selecting a preset will immediately populate all CSP fields and clear any previous values. Make sure to save your current configuration before trying a preset if you want to keep it."
msgstr ""

